  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      How effective is sugar in reducing the debriding of sloughy, necrotic or infected exudating
      wounds compared with standard treatment?
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients for whom all the following apply:

      Have an exudating wound sizes 5cm2 and 40cm2 A minimum of 25% slough, infected and necrotic
      tissue No dry necrotic eschar present Ankle Brachial Pressure Index of greater than 0.6 Are
      over 18 years Independently and willingly consent
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
